This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Makayla Diana Taylor not in court.  
Attorney Sylvan Jaspen in court for Makayla Diana Taylor.  
Attorney Erika Strebel in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case calendared for a Scheduling Conference. DEFENDANT FAILED TO APPEAR. 
Defense has no explanation for defendants non appearance and  request a calendar call date.  
Court ordered bench warrant issued, Remand to the Judge and STAYED issuance until the next court date.
Court ordered matter adjourned back to Branch 19. This hearing will be in person.
Calendar call scheduled for November 11, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Makayla Diana Taylor appeared by video.  Attorney Sylvan Jaspen appeared by video for Makayla Diana Taylor.  Prosecuting attorney Arthur Kenneth Thexton in court in person for the State of Wisconsin. 
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Court took judicial notice of case #22CF463. Sworn for the State: MPD Officer R. Stoiber. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 19.
Scheduling conference scheduled for October 26, 2022 at 03:00 pm.
Justice Point Pretrial Services VIOLATION Report received and filed.
Justice Point Pretrial Services VIOLATION Report.
Oral No Contact Order.  Defendant to have NO VIOLENT contact with ACP.

Court orders defendant TURNED OVER to JUSTICE Point for Level 5 Supervision.      
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defense counsel acknowledge receipt of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.
Defense enters a plea of NOT GUILTY as to misdemeanor count 1 and 2. 
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.

Defendant Makayla Diana Taylor in court with attorney Sylvan Jaspen.  Defendant Makayla Diana Taylor in custody.  William R. F. Ackell for Alexandria Carlson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case in court for return on doctors report. Court reviews doctor's report with the parties.  State, defense counsel and defendant are not challenging the findings of the doctor's report.
Court  adopts the professional opinion of the examiner's that the defendant does not lack substantial capacity to understand the proceedings or aid in his/her defense. 
Court finds defendant competent and reinstates the proceedings.  Case remains calendared in Branch 19.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 20, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Attorney Sylvan Jaspen in court, defendant Makayla Diana Taylor not in court, in custody.  Alexandria S. Carlson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case heard in Br. 25 for Br. 45.  Doctor review the case has requested an extension to complete the doctor's report. Matter remains calendared in Br. 45.   Pursuant to Chief Judge Directive 22-04, parties are hereby notified that as of July 30, 2022, this case will be assigned to Branch 19, Judge Kori Ashley, in Room 313 of the Safety Building.  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for August 5, 2022 at 09:30 am.
Received and Filed. Competency Evaluation Extension Letter

Defendant Makayla Diana Taylor in court with attorney Matthew V Plummer.  Defendant Makayla Diana Taylor in custody.  Alexander James Geocaris appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
   Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court found probable cause and ordered defendant examined by the Forensic Unit.  Order for Examination, signed and filed.   Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Kies, Branch 45.   Court ordered defendant REMANDED into custody of Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for July 18, 2022 at 08:30 am.
